{
  "texts": [
    "The class score of bounding boxes is relatively easy to measure and quantify using similar approaches to the classification task.",
    "However, estimating the accuracy of bounding boxes and the number of bounding boxes recalled is a hard problem in the absence of the ground truth.",
    "Our approach is to use a learning-based module, e.g., a lightweight binary classifier.",
    "The classifier takes some extracted features (intermediate or output features) from the exit branch and outputs a scalar value (in [0, 1]), indicating the confidence in the outputs of the exit branch.",
    "A high value indicates that the output (prediction) of the exit branch is likely accurate."
  ]
}